{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RGSfYrtUz94uYSa3F2TEFm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The root cause is clear:\n\nThe ConfigMap `es-config` has `node.name: ` (empty value) in the `elasticsearch.yml`. This was set by the precondition script which used a heredoc with `${POD_NAME}` that didn't get substituted (it was in single quotes in the heredoc, so the variable wasn't expanded).\n\nThe other two nodes (es-cluster-0 and es-cluster-1) use a StatefulSet that likely sets the `POD_NAME` env variable and passes it to Elasticsearch via environment variable substitution in the config file. Let me check the StatefulSet spec.\nSo the issue is that `POD_NAME` wasn't set in the shell environment when the precondition script ran, causing the variable to expand to an empty string in the ConfigMap. The other two nodes are running fine because they're using a different mechanism to set the node name. Ah, that makes sense—es-cluster-0 and es-cluster-1 were already running with the old ConfigMap before it got overwritten, so they kept their original node names, but es-cluster-2 got restarted after the ConfigMap was replaced with the broken version. I need to restore the ConfigMap with the correct `node.name: ${POD_NAME}` syntax and also verify the seed hosts are pointing to the right namespace instead of `default.svc.cluster.local`. Let me check the original resource files to see what the ConfigMap and StatefulSet should look like.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1988,"cache_read_input_tokens":32013,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1988},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f7e58f3-8ff3-440c-a527-37d4f124d3d5","uuid":"44f95470-45eb-428b-bc13-d27502ba5800","request_id":"req_011CcQB7mfiq6boqzg9jjJwV"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RGSfYrtUz94uYSa3F2TEFm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found the issue. The ConfigMap has `node.name: ` (empty) because the heredoc in the precondition script shell-expanded `${POD_NAME}` to nothing, overwriting the correct config. `es-cluster-2` was restarted after this bad ConfigMap was applied, so only it crashes. Let me check the StatefulSet to understand the intended config pattern."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1988,"cache_read_input_tokens":32013,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1988},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f7e58f3-8ff3-440c-a527-37d4f124d3d5","uuid":"848a478a-d608-4fbb-835b-cd5addd62cb2","request_id":"req_011CcQB7mfiq6boqzg9jjJwV"}
