{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PthDD9EB6HDqrnaqi2vhzq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three verification conditions are met:\n\n1. **Cluster health: green** — `status: green`, no unassigned shards.\n2. **All 3 nodes in `/_cat/nodes`** — `es-cluster-0`, `es-cluster-1`, and `es-cluster-2` all appear.\n3. **`app-data` readable** — search returns the seeded document.\n\n**Root cause:** The precondition script applied a ConfigMap via a heredoc that shell-expanded `${POD_NAME}` to an empty string, leaving `node.name: ` blank. Since the ConfigMap uses `subPath` mounting, `es-cluster-2` (restarted after the broken ConfigMap was applied) read the empty `node.name` and crashed on every restart.\n\n**Fix:** Restored the original ConfigMap (with literal `${POD_NAME}` for Elasticsearch's own env-var substitution and correct short-form seed hosts), then deleted `es-cluster-2` so the StatefulSet controller recreated it with the correct config."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1046,"cache_read_input_tokens":39325,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1046},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f7e58f3-8ff3-440c-a527-37d4f124d3d5","uuid":"1e172e26-6298-471c-99f4-fa8b0a6bec34","request_id":"req_011CcQBGJWqEre2nnNFUnmAT"}
